# Application stack & dependencies

Values below mirror `package.json`. Caret (`^`) means compatible upgrades within the semver range; exact pins are fixed until changed in `package.json`.

## Core runtime

| Package      | Version | Role                        |
| ------------ | ------- | --------------------------- |
| `next`       | 16.2.1  | App Router, SSR, API routes |
| `react`      | 19.2.4  | UI                          |
| `react-dom`  | 19.2.4  | DOM rendering               |
| `typescript` | ^5      | Language / compiler         |

## Styling

| Package                | Version | Role                               |
| ---------------------- | ------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `tailwindcss`          | ^4      | Utility-first CSS                  |
| `@tailwindcss/postcss` | ^4      | PostCSS integration for Tailwind 4 |

## Data & external services

| Package                 | Version  | Role                                                  |
| ----------------------- | -------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| `@supabase/supabase-js` | ^2.100.1 | Supabase client (DB / server usage per project rules) |
| `brapi`                 | ^1.0.1   | Brazilian market data API (server-side)               |
| `twelvedata`            | ^3.0.1   | Market data API (e.g. US / global)                    |

## Tooling (dev)

| Package              | Version | Role                                              |
| -------------------- | ------- | ------------------------------------------------- |
| `eslint`             | ^9      | Linting                                           |
| `eslint-config-next` | 16.2.1  | Next.js + React ESLint preset (aligned with Next) |
| `tsx`                | ^4.21.0 | Run TypeScript scripts (e.g. `scripts/sync-*.ts`) |
| `dotenv`             | ^17.4.2 | Load `.env` in Node scripts                       |
| `@types/node`        | ^20     | Node typings                                      |
| `@types/react`       | ^19     | React typings                                     |
| `@types/react-dom`   | ^19     | React DOM typings                                 |

## npm scripts (reference)

- `dev` / `build` / `start` / `lint` — Next.js + ESLint
- `sync-cotacoes` / `sync-cotacoes-us` — `tsx` entrypoints for sync scripts

When bumping major versions, check release notes for Next, React, Tailwind, and ESLint together; align `eslint-config-next` with `next` when the project pins both.
